        {%- assign faqs = "
          Who delivers Core Services?|Core Services are delivered by experienced business practitioners — not AI tools, not generalist freelancers. Each service is reviewed and completed by a practitioner with relevant expertise in that service category.||
          How long does delivery take?|Delivery timeframes vary by service and complexity. The Business Health Check typically delivers within 3–5 business days. Advisory services and Decision Desk are typically 5–7 business days. The Fixer timeframe is agreed after intake review. Members receive priority processing.||
          Do I need to be a member to use Core Services?|No. All Core Services are available individually at standard pricing. Membership provides $0 access to all Core Services plus the broader platform — making it the most cost-effective path if you anticipate using more than one service.||
          What happens after I complete the intake form?|Your intake is reviewed by a practitioner assigned to your service type. You'll receive confirmation of your intake submission via email. The practitioner will complete the service and deliver the output within the agreed timeframe.||
          Can I get a refund if I'm not satisfied?|Core Services are practitioner-delivered engagements. If there's a service quality issue, contact us directly at /pages/contact and we will review the situation. We aim to resolve quality concerns with re-delivery or appropriate remedy.||
          What's the difference between a Core Service and an On-Demand Service?|Core Services are structured, fixed-scope advisory engagements delivered by an RBP practitioner. On-Demand Services are specialist service products spanning specific functions (accounting, legal, digital, HR, etc.) delivered by vetted providers. Core Services are about clarity and decisions; On-Demand Services are about specialist execution.||
          How does the member discount work?|Members tagged with the appropriate membership tier tag receive an automatic 100% discount on Core Services at checkout. This discount is applied automatically — you don't need a coupon code. The discount is live once the Shopify discount rule is activated for your account.||
          Can I use The Fixer if I don't know exactly what the problem is?|Yes. The Fixer intake form is designed to help you articulate the problem. If you're unsure whether The Fixer is the right service, start with the Business Health Check — it will identify the right pathway for you.
        " | split: "||" -%}

